{{about|the Irish Parliament Act of 1697|the American Revolutionary War act of 1778|Massachusetts Banishment Act}} {{Infobox UK legislation |short_title = Banishment Act |parliament = Parliament of Ireland |long_title = An Act for banishing all Papists exercising any Ecclesiastical Jurisdiction, and all Regulars of the Popish Clergy out of this Kingdom |year = 1697 |statute_book_chapter = 9 Will III c.1 |introduced_by = |territorial_extent = |royal_assent = |commencement = |repeal_date = |amendments = |primary_legislation = |related_legislation = |repealing_legislation= |status = Repealed |original_text = |legislation_history = |use_new_UK-LEG = |revised_text = }}
The '''Banishment Act''' was an [[Act of Parliament|Act]] of the [[Parliament of Ireland]] (citation 9 Will III c.1), one of a series of [[Irish Penal Laws|Penal Laws]] passed in 1697 that banished all [[bishop]]s of the [[Roman Catholic Church]] from [[Ireland]] to protect the official [[state church]], the [[Church of Ireland]]. The [[long title]] of the Act is "An Act for banishing all Papists exercising any Ecclesiastical Jurisdiction, and all Regulars of the Popish Clergy out of this Kingdom."
