'''''Broken Promise''''' ({{lang-sk|Nedodržaný sľub}}) is a 2009 [[drama film]] directed by [[Jiří Chlumský]] and starring {{ill|Samuel Spišák|sk}}, [[Ondřej Vetchý]] and {{ill|Zuzana Porubjaková|sk}}. The film was Slovakia's submission to the [[82nd Academy Awards]] for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.screendaily.com/jiri-chlumskys-broken-promise-selected-as-slovakias-oscar-entry/5006257.article|title=Jiri Chlumsky's Broken Promise selected as Slovakia's Oscar entry|work=screendaily.com|date=30 September 2009|accessdate=12 February 2018}}</ref> The film won the main prize at the 2009 Los Angeles Jewish Film Festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cas.sk/clanok/116999/nedodrzany-slub-ziskal-hlavnu-cenu-na-festivale-v-los-angeles/|title=Nedodržaný sľub získal hlavnú cenu na festivale v Los Angeles|language=sk|work=cas.sk|date=14 May 2009|accessdate=12 February 2018}}</ref> ''Broken Promise'' received nine nominations at the 2010 [[Sun in a Net Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://aktualne.centrum.sk/nedodrzany-slub-a-pokoj-v-dusi-po-9-nominacii-na-slovenskych-oscarov/showbizz/film/|title=Nedodržaný sľub a Pokoj v duši po 9 nominácii na slovenských Oscarov|language=sk|work=centrum.sk|date=21 April 2010|accessdate=12 February 2018}}</ref> but succeeded in winning just one, awarded to [[Michal Novinski]] for the film's music.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kinema.sk/novinka/5732/ocenenia-slnko-v-sieti-2010.htm|title=Ocenenia Slnko v sieti 2010|language=sk|work=kinema.sk|date=28 April 2010|accessdate=12 February 2018}}</ref>

